---
description: Tests with behavior changes; no fabricated results
alwaysApply: true
---

# Testing

- Ship or update tests when behavior changes, unless an explicit justified exception is documented in the PR/plan.
- **Never fabricate test results** — Do not invent pass/fail output, coverage numbers, or “green CI” claims.
- Only report tests that were actually executed; include the command and observed outcome.
- If tests could not run (missing deps, env, infra), say so clearly — do not imply success.
- Prefer focused tests that assert the changed behavior over broad, flaky suites.
